	(text "[1] We're placing these resistors because of bad past experience with linear\nregulators, when using ceramic capacitors at the output. Turns out that, if\nthe ESR of the output capacitor is too low, the output might oscillate around\nthe regulated value. This is not a big problem when using electrolytic capacitors,\nbecause of their comparatively higher ESR. Anyways, theses resistors should be\nsmall, something like 1R or even smaller. However, they might make difference."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 117.094 26.67 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left bottom)
